Cohn-D.

Multilobular biliary cirrhosis of the liver associated with cystic
fibrosis (mucoviscidosis).

CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: co.  LIVER-CIRRHOSIS-BILIARY: et.

ADULT.  AUTOPSY.  CASE-REPORT.  HUMAN.  MALE.

A case (including autopsy findings) is reported of multilobular
biliary cirrhosis with a strictly nodular liver developing in a 20-
year-old male with cystic fibrosis (mucoviscidosis). The pathogenesis
of biliary cirrhosis in cystic fibrosis is briefly discussed.

